I think it is important to show that men are not necessarily against women in technology. Many women actually don't go into computing because other women are competitive and hold them back. I noticed that a lot of the girls bragged about their skills, which can discourage those who haven't had the opportunities they have. I think an emphasis should be placed on simply helping women to learn how to navigate computing careers and how to deal with other women who hold them back, as well as how to appropriately communicate your skills without discouraging others from the field.
